<title>USA: Stanhome completes Hamilton sale.</title>
<headline>Stanhome completes Hamilton sale.</headline>
<dateline>WESTFIELD, Mass. 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Stanhome Inc said Friday it had completed the previously announced sale of its Hamilton Direct Response businesses to Bradford Group, a privately held marketer of giftwares, for about $46 million, including the assumption of intercompany debt.</p>
<p>With the sale, Stanhome's Enesco Giftware subsidiary and Bradford also entered into a long-term agreement for Bradford to sell Enesco products under license, generating a stream of royalty income for the company.</p>
<p>Stanhome said it continues to evaluate alternatives for its Worldwide Direct Selling Group.</p>
